7
00:00:26.160 --> 00:00:30.880
To Sherlock Holmes she is always the woman.

8
00:00:30.880 --> 00:00:36.080
I have seldom heard him mention her under any other name.

9
00:00:36.080 --> 00:00:42.080
In his eyes she eclipses and predominates the whole of her sex.

10
00:00:42.080 --> 00:00:48.120
It was not that he felt any emotion akin to love for Irene Adler.

11
00:00:48.120 --> 00:00:55.200
All emotions and that one particularly were apparent to his cold, precise, but admirably

12
00:00:55.200 --> 00:00:58.040
balanced mind.

13
00:00:58.040 --> 00:01:05.720
He was, I take it, the most perfect reasoning and observing machine that the world has seen.

14
00:01:05.720 --> 00:01:11.280
But as a lover he would have placed himself in a false position.

15
00:01:11.280 --> 00:01:17.880
He never spoke of the softer passions, save with a jive and a snare.

16
00:01:17.880 --> 00:01:21.880
They were admirable things for the observer.

17
00:01:21.880 --> 00:01:26.600
And for drawing the veil from men's motives and actions.

18
00:01:26.600 --> 00:01:32.800
But for the trained reasoner to admit such intrusions into his own delicate and finally

19
00:01:32.800 --> 00:01:38.960
adjusted temperament was to introduce a distracting factor, which might throw a doubt upon all

20
00:01:38.960 --> 00:01:41.760
his mental results.

21
00:01:41.760 --> 00:01:48.200
Grit in a sensitive instrument or a crack in one of his own high power lenses would not

22
00:01:48.200 --> 00:01:54.400
be more disturbing than a strong emotion in a nature such as his.

23
00:01:54.400 --> 00:01:58.320
And yet there was but one woman to him.

24
00:01:58.320 --> 00:02:06.280
