25
00:02:06.280 --> 00:02:09.800
I had seen little of Holmes lately.

26
00:02:09.800 --> 00:02:13.520
My marriage had drifted us away from each other.

27
00:02:13.520 --> 00:02:20.120
My own complete happiness and the home-centered interests which rise up around the man who first

28
00:02:20.120 --> 00:02:26.960
finds himself master of his own establishment were sufficient to absorb all my attention.

29
00:02:26.960 --> 00:02:33.360
While Holmes, who loathed every form of society with his whole behemian soul, remained in our

30
00:02:33.360 --> 00:02:40.200
lodgings in Baker Street, buried among his old books, and alternating from week to week

31
00:02:40.200 --> 00:02:43.320
between cocaine and ambition.

32
00:02:43.320 --> 00:02:49.960
The drowsiness of the drug and the fierce energy of his own keen nature.

33
00:02:49.960 --> 00:02:56.600
He was still as ever deeply attracted by the study of crime and occupied his immense

34
