Our visitor glanced with some apparent surprise at the languid, lounging figure of the man

233
00:19:12.920 --> 00:19:19.200
who had been no doubt depicted to him as the most incisive reasoner and most energetic

234
00:19:19.200 --> 00:19:22.360
agent in Europe.

235
00:19:22.360 --> 00:19:27.960
Holmes slowly reopened his eyes and looked impatiently at his gigantic client.

236
00:19:27.960 --> 00:19:35.120
"'If your majesty would condescend to state your case,' he remarked, "'I should be

237
00:19:35.120 --> 00:19:38.440
better able to advise you.'

238
00:19:38.440 --> 00:19:45.080
The man sprang from his chair and paced up and down the room in uncontrollable agitation.

239
00:19:45.080 --> 00:19:50.600
Then with a gesture of desperation he tore the mask from his face and hurled it upon the

240
00:19:50.600 --> 00:19:51.600
ground.

241
00:19:51.600 --> 00:19:55.280
"'You are I'd,' he cried, "'I am the king.

242
00:19:55.280 --> 00:19:58.800
Why should I attempt to conceal it?'

243
00:19:58.800 --> 00:20:02.320
"'I indeed,' murmured Holmes.

244
00:20:02.320 --> 00:20:08.840
Your majesty had not spoken before I was aware that I was addressing Wilhelm Gottzreich

245
00:20:08.840 --> 00:20:17.400
Sigis Mond von Ormstein, Grand Duke of Castle Felstein and hereditary king of Bohemia.

246
00:20:17.400 --> 00:20:23.360
"'But you can understand,' said a strange visitor, sitting down once more and passing

247
00:20:23.360 --> 00:20:26.160
his hand over his high white forehead.

248
00:20:26.160 --> 00:20:33.240
"'You can understand that I am not accustomed to doing such business in my own person.

249
00:20:33.240 --> 00:20:40.080
Yet the matter was so delicate that I could not confide it to an agent without putting

250
00:20:40.080 --> 00:20:43.360
myself in his power.

251
00:20:43.360 --> 00:20:49.880
I have come incognito from Prague for the purpose of consulting you.'

252
00:20:49.880 --> 00:20:56.520
"'Then pray consult,' said Holmes, shutting his eyes once more.

253
00:20:56.520 --> 00:20:59.640
The facts are briefly these.

254
00:20:59.640 --> 00:21:07.240
Some five years ago, during a lengthy visit to Warsaw, I made a acquaintance of the well-known

255
00:21:07.240 --> 00:21:11.680
adventurice, Irene Adler.

256
00:21:11.680 --> 00:21:16.440
Her name is no doubt familiar to you.'

257
00:21:16.440 --> 00:21:19.800
Kindly look her up in my index, Doctor.

258
00:21:19.800 --> 00:21:23.920
Murmord Holmes, without opening his eyes.

259
00:21:23.920 --> 00:21:30.600
For many years he had adopted a system of docketing all paragraphs concerning men and things,

260
00:21:30.600 --> 00:21:35.280
so that it was difficult to name a subject or a person on which he could not at once

261
00:21:35.280 --> 00:21:38.240
furnish information.

262
00:21:38.240 --> 00:21:44.080
In this case I found her biography sandwiched in between that of a Hebrew rabbi and that

263
00:21:44.080 --> 00:21:48.600
of a staff commander who had written a monograph upon the deep sea fishes.

264
00:21:48.600 --> 00:21:52.480
"'Let me see,' said Holmes.

265
00:21:52.480 --> 00:21:59.320
"'Mmm, born in New Jersey in the year 1858.

266
00:21:59.320 --> 00:22:01.320
Contralto.

267
00:22:01.320 --> 00:22:04.320
La Scala.

268
00:22:04.320 --> 00:22:10.760
Prima Donna Imperial Opera of Warsaw, yes.

269
00:22:10.760 --> 00:22:13.560
Retired from operatic stage?

270
00:22:13.560 --> 00:22:17.800
Ah, living in London, quite so.

271
00:22:17.800 --> 00:22:23.680
Your majesty, as I understand, became entangled with this young person.

272
00:22:23.680 --> 00:22:30.600
Wrote her some compromising letters, and is now desirous of getting those letters back.

273
00:22:30.600 --> 00:22:33.320
Preciously so.

274
00:22:33.320 --> 00:22:35.360
But how?

275
00:22:35.360 --> 00:22:37.760
Was there a secret marriage?

276
00:22:37.760 --> 00:22:38.760
None.

277
00:22:38.760 --> 00:22:42.280
No legal papers or certificates.

278
00:22:42.280 --> 00:22:43.280
None.

279
00:22:43.280 --> 00:22:47.200
Then I failed to follow your majesty.

280
00:22:47.200 --> 00:22:54.480
If this young person should produce her letters for blackmailing or other purposes, how

281
00:22:54.480 --> 00:22:58.120
is she to prove their authenticity?

282
00:22:58.120 --> 00:23:00.080
There is writing.

283
00:23:00.080 --> 00:23:03.000
Puff, forgery.

284
00:23:03.000 --> 00:23:05.760
My private note paper.

285
00:23:05.760 --> 00:23:06.760
Stolen.

286
00:23:06.760 --> 00:23:09.600
My own seal.

287
00:23:09.600 --> 00:23:11.680
Immitated.

288
00:23:11.680 --> 00:23:13.760
My photograph.

289
00:23:13.760 --> 00:23:15.760
Bought.

290
00:23:15.760 --> 00:23:18.840
The above both in the photograph.

291
00:23:18.840 --> 00:23:19.960
Oh dear.

292
00:23:19.960 --> 00:23:24.240
That is very bad.

293
00:23:24.240 --> 00:23:28.240
Your majesty has indeed committed an indiscretion.

294
00:23:29.240 --> 00:23:32.560
I was mad in saying.

295
00:23:32.560 --> 00:23:36.040
You have compromised yourself seriously.

296
00:23:36.040 --> 00:23:38.320
I was only calm, Princeton.

297
00:23:38.320 --> 00:23:39.720
I was young.

298
00:23:39.720 --> 00:23:42.440
I am at thirty now.

299
00:23:42.440 --> 00:23:44.520
It must be recovered.

300
00:23:44.520 --> 00:23:48.240
If you have tied and failed.

301
00:23:48.240 --> 00:23:50.000
Your majesty must pay.

302
00:23:50.000 --> 00:23:52.000
It must be bought.

303
00:23:52.000 --> 00:23:54.560
She will not sell.

304
00:23:54.560 --> 00:23:56.080
Stolen then.

305
00:23:56.080 --> 00:23:59.560
Five attempts have been made.

306
00:23:59.560 --> 00:24:02.800
Twice burglars in my pay ransacked her house.

307
00:24:02.800 --> 00:24:06.160
Once they diverted her luggage when she travelled.

308
00:24:06.160 --> 00:24:07.880
Twice she has been veiled.

309
00:24:07.880 --> 00:24:10.320
There has been no result.

310
00:24:10.320 --> 00:24:12.400
No sign of it.

311
00:24:12.400 --> 00:24:15.560
Absolutely none.

312
00:24:15.560 --> 00:24:16.560
Holmes laughed.

313
00:24:16.560 --> 00:24:21.640
It is quite a pretty little problem, said he.

314
00:24:21.640 --> 00:24:28.280
What a very serious one to me, returned the king reproachfully.

315
00:24:28.280 --> 00:24:34.400
Very indeed, and what does she propose to do with the photograph?

316
00:24:34.400 --> 00:24:36.600
To ruin me.

317
00:24:36.600 --> 00:24:37.600
But how?

318
00:24:37.600 --> 00:24:41.440
I am about to be married.

319
00:24:41.440 --> 00:24:43.720
So I have heard.

320
00:24:43.720 --> 00:24:50.720
To clothe tilde Lortmann, Fond Sucks, Minning and second daughter of the King of Scandinavia.

321
00:24:50.720 --> 00:24:54.520
You may know the strict principles of her family.

322
00:24:54.520 --> 00:24:58.400
She is herself the very soul of delicacy.

323
00:24:58.400 --> 00:25:04.760
A shadow of a doubt has to my conduct would bring the matter to an end.

324
00:25:04.760 --> 00:25:07.240
And Rainy Adler?

325
00:25:07.240 --> 00:25:11.240
Threatens to send them the photograph, and she will do it.

326
00:25:11.240 --> 00:25:13.720
I know that she will do it.

327
00:25:13.720 --> 00:25:18.320
You do not know her, but she has a soul of steel.

328
00:25:18.320 --> 00:25:26.160
She has the face of the most beautiful women, and the mind of the most isolated Lortmann.

329
00:25:26.160 --> 00:25:30.840
Rather than I should marry another woman, there are no lengths to which she would not go

330
00:25:30.840 --> 00:25:31.840
none.

331
00:25:31.840 --> 00:25:35.600
You are sure that she has not sent it yet?

332
00:25:35.600 --> 00:25:37.920
I am sure.

333
00:25:37.920 --> 00:25:39.720
And why?

334
00:25:39.720 --> 00:25:44.320
Because she has said that she would send it on the day when the betrothal was publicly

335
00:25:44.320 --> 00:25:46.080
proclaimed.

336
00:25:46.080 --> 00:25:48.480
That will be next Monday.

337
00:25:48.480 --> 00:25:52.960
Oh, then we have three days yet.

338
00:25:52.960 --> 00:25:54.840
Said Holmes with a yawn.

339
00:25:54.840 --> 00:25:59.760
That is very fortunate as I have one or two matters of importance to look into just

340
00:25:59.760 --> 00:26:01.640
at present.

341
00:26:01.640 --> 00:26:05.560
Your Majesty will, of course, stay in London for the present.

342
00:26:05.560 --> 00:26:06.560
Certainly.

343
00:26:06.560 --> 00:26:12.040
You will find me at the langum under the name of the Count Fond Corm.

344
00:26:12.040 --> 00:26:16.840
Then I shall drop you a line to let you know how we progress.

345
00:26:16.840 --> 00:26:18.400
Pray do so.

346
00:26:18.400 --> 00:26:22.440
I shall be all anxiety.

347
00:26:22.440 --> 00:26:27.360
Then as to money, you have carte blanche.

348
00:26:27.360 --> 00:26:29.360
Absolutely.

349
00:26:29.360 --> 00:26:36.040
I tell you that I could give one of the provinces of my kingdom to have that photograph.

350
00:26:36.040 --> 00:26:39.160
And for present expenses.

351
00:26:39.160 --> 00:26:44.360
The king took a heavy chamileather bag from under his cloak and laid it on the table.

352
00:26:44.360 --> 00:26:51.120
There are three hundred pounds in gold and seven hundred in notes, he said.

353
00:26:51.120 --> 00:26:56.680
Holmes scribbled a receipt upon a sheet of his notebook and handed it to him.

354
00:26:56.680 --> 00:27:04.640
And Mamm Zell's address, he asked, is Brianny Lodge serpentine Avignon St. John's

355
00:27:04.640 --> 00:27:05.640
Wood?

356
00:27:05.640 --> 00:27:08.080
Holmes took a note of it.

357
00:27:08.080 --> 00:27:11.040
One other question, said he.

358
00:27:11.040 --> 00:27:13.760
Was the photograph a cabinet?

359
00:27:13.760 --> 00:27:15.880
It was.

360
00:27:15.880 --> 00:27:18.760
Then good night, Your Majesty.

361
00:27:18.760 --> 00:27:23.640
And I trusted we shall soon have some good news for you.

362
00:27:23.640 --> 00:27:25.680
And good night Watson.

363
00:27:25.680 --> 00:27:30.720
He added as the wheels of the Royal Brom rolled down the street.

364
00:27:30.720 --> 00:27:35.880
If you will be good enough to call tomorrow afternoon at three o'clock, I should like

365
00:27:35.880 --> 00:27:41.200
to chat this little matter over with you.

366
00:27:41.200 --> 00:27:45.400
End of part one of Adventure One, a scandal in Bohemia.

